# Website Deploy Rule

This repository owns the public Goalrail website only. Website deployment is
handled by the GitOps entrypoint in `/Users/vi/personal/standalone/infra` and is
separate from the Goalrail app/server, desktop releases, package publishing,
Cloudflare Workers, Vercel, and any infrastructure in `heurema/goalrail`.

## Scope

- Deploy only this repo: `heurema/goalrail-site`.
- Deploy only the public website served at `https://goalrail.dev`.
- Keep app builds separate. If the request also mentions desktop/iOS/app builds,
  use the app build instructions in `heurema/goalrail` and do not treat them as
  part of the website server deploy.
- Do not run `wrangler deploy`.
- Do not run app/server deploys, package releases, image publishing, Vercel
  import/deploy, or release workflows from `heurema/goalrail`.
- Do not bump package/app versions for a build-only task. Version changes happen
  only when the user explicitly asks for a release/version bump.
- Do not invent server hosts, paths, credentials, service names, or restart
  commands. Production is updated by the infra GitOps script, not direct SSH.

## Required Inputs

The approved deploy entrypoint is:

```bash
cd /Users/vi/personal/standalone/infra
scripts/deploy-goalrail-site.sh --commit-push --reconcile
```

The script resolves `/Users/vi/personal/heurema/goalrail-site` `HEAD`, verifies
that the commit is already reachable from `origin/main`, updates
`GOALRAIL_SITE_REF` in
`kubernetes/apps/heurema/prod/goalrail-site/values.yaml`, validates Kustomize,
commits and pushes the infra GitOps change, reconciles Flux and the HelmRelease,
then verifies the deployed ref and rollout.

If the site commit is not reachable from `origin/main`, stop and land/push the
site change first. Do not bypass this by deploying a private branch ref unless
the user explicitly asks for a one-off production override.

## Local Gate

Run these checks before any server change:

```bash
git status --short --branch
bun install --frozen-lockfile
bun run strip-lock-proxy:check
bun run lint
bun run lint:links
bun run test:theme
bun run test:go-routes
bun run build
```

If any check fails, do not deploy. Fix the site or report the blocker.

## Deploy Flow

After the local gate passes, land and push the site change to `origin/main`.
Then deploy through infra:

```bash
cd /Users/vi/personal/standalone/infra
git status --short --branch
scripts/deploy-goalrail-site.sh --commit-push --reconcile
```

Keep secrets out of logs. Never print env files, tokens, private SSH config, or
process manager secrets.

## Post-Deploy Gate

After deployment, verify the public site:

```bash
curl -fsSI https://goalrail.dev/
curl -fsSI https://goalrail.dev/en
curl -fsSI https://goalrail.dev/ru
curl -fsS https://goalrail.dev/llms.txt >/dev/null
```

Report the branch, commit SHA, checks run, deploy entrypoint used, and smoke-test
results. If the deploy was blocked, report the exact missing input or failing
command.
